Kaizer Chiefs were held to a one all draw by Bloemfontein Celtic at the Free State Stadium on Sunday afternoon.Chiefs defender Eric Mathoho&#8217;s header finds the back of the net for Amakhosi in the 37th minute of the game after a good deliverance coming from the corner kick that was taken by Keagan Buchanan.Chiefs held onto the lead until the two clubs went to half time.Bloemfontein Celtic got an equaliser in the second half from the substitute Atusaye Nyondo who came in for Roggert Nyundu in the 67th minute of the game. Celtic got a penalty in the 75th minute and striker Nyondo simply put the ball behind the net.-TNA Reporter